Set oven rack about 6 inches from the heat source and preheat the oven's broiler. Heat olive oil in an oven-proof 12-inch skillet over medium heat; stir in SPAM(R) Classic and cook, stirring occasionally, until browned, 6 to 8 minutes. Stir garlic into skillet; cook until fragrant, 1 to 2 minutes more. Stir Swiss chard into skillet; cook until wilted, 5 to 10 minutes. Tear bread into chunks; process in food processor until the size of breadcrumbs. Top Swiss chard mixture with shredded Swiss cheese, then top with breadcrumbs; drizzle olive oil over the top. Place skillet under broiler until breadcrumbs start to brown, about 2 minutes.